<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Revoked on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/revoked/</link><description>Recent content in Revoked on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/revoked/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] C Certificate has been revoked</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/certificate-revoked/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/certificate-revoked/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="certificate-has-been-revoked"&gt;Certificate has been revoked&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A revoked certificate is one that has been invalidated before its expiry date. The certificate authority has explicitly marked it as no longer trustworthy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 1: Private key compromised
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Server admin revoked cert after key leak
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 2: CA policy violation
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Certificate found to violate CA policy
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 3: Domain ownership change
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Certificate revoked when domain changed hands
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-get-a-new-certificate"&gt;Fix 1: Get a new certificate&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Generate new CSR and get signed&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;openssl req -new -key server.key -out server.csr
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-check-crl-certificate-revocation-list"&gt;Fix 2: Check CRL (Certificate Revocation List)&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;openssl s_client -connect example.com:443 -crl_check
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-handle-in-application"&gt;Fix 3: Handle in application&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;long&lt;/span&gt; verify_result &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;SSL_get_verify_result&lt;/span&gt;(ssl);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (verify_result &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;==&lt;/span&gt; X509_V_ERR_CERT_REVOKED) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;fprintf&lt;/span&gt;(stderr, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Certificate has been revoked&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;\n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;SSL_shutdown&lt;/span&gt;(ssl);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/certificate-expired/"&gt;Certificate expired&lt;/a&gt; — expired certificate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/tls-handshake-failure/"&gt;TLS handshake failure&lt;/a&gt; — general TLS error.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/self-signed-certificate/"&gt;Self-signed certificate&lt;/a&gt; — untrusted cert.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Linux KEYREVOKED (errno 85) — Key Has Been Revoked Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/linux/errno-85/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/linux/errno-85/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="linux-keyrevoked-errno-85--key-has-been-revoked"&gt;Linux KEYREVOKED (errno 85) — Key Has Been Revoked&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;KEYREVOKED (errno 85) means the cryptographic key has been explicitly revoked. This error occurs when a program tries to use a key that has been invalidated by an administrator or security policy. It is distinct from KEYEXPIRED (errno 84) because KEYREVOKED indicates intentional revocation, not natural expiration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Key was revoked by an administrator&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Security policy invalidated the key&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Kerberos principal was disabled or revoked&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Key was compromised and invalidated&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix-keyrevoked"&gt;How to Fix KEYREVOKED&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="1-check-key-revocation-status"&gt;1. Check Key Revocation Status&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Verify if keys have been revoked:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>